summary_markdown: This data presents a comparative analysis of brand strength growth between 2007 and 2010, ranking ten distinct brands by their percentage increase. Facebook exhibited the most significant growth at 195%, followed by Skype with 79% and YouTube with 78%. Other brands showing substantial growth include Netflix (72%), Samsung (66%), and Apple (51%). Brands with more moderate growth rates were iTunes (50%), Amazon.com (44%), Reese’s (42%), and National Guard (35%). The structure is a simple ranking, highlighting the varying degrees of brand strength expansion across different industries and product categories within the specified timeframe.
